ssets.com/115049/1705074203-screenshot-2024-01-12-at-15-37-40.png?auto=format&w=2880","srcSet":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/115049/1705074203-screenshot-2024-01-12-at-15-37-40.png?auto=format&dpr=0.25&w=2880 720w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/115049/1705074203-screenshot-2024-01-12-at-15-37-40.png?auto=format&dpr=0.5&w=2880 1440w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/115049/1705074203-screenshot-2024-01-12-at-15-37-40.png?auto=format&w=2880 2880w","sizes":"(min-width: 2880px) 2880px, 100vw"}},"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"width":2880,"height":1800},"alt":"design"}}],"html":"<p></p><hr><h1>Project Overview</h1><h2>Duration</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Jan 2023 - Feb 2023</strong></p></li></ul><h2>Project Type</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Solo Project</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Public Repository</strong></p></li></ul><h2>Technologies</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Programming Language:</strong> C++</p></li><li><p><strong>Microcontroller:</strong> Arduino (ESP8266)</p></li><li><p><strong>Testing Framework:</strong> Gtest</p></li><li><p><strong>Platform:</strong> PlatformIO</p></li><li><p><strong>Components:</strong> ESP32, Embedded IC, NeoPixel RGB LED (WS2812)</p></li></ul><h2>Project Links</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Repository:</strong> <a target=\"_new\" href=\"\">Link to Repo</a></p></li><li><p><strong>Instructable:</strong> <a target=\"_new\" href=\"\">Link to Instructable</a></p></li></ul><h1>Project Details</h1><h2>Description</h2><p>The Brolli project is an Arduino program designed for an ESP8266 module, NeoPixel LED strip, and Wi-Fi connectivity to provide a visual indication of hourly precipitation probability for a specific location. It fetches weather forecast data from the Open Meteo API and uses NeoPixel LEDs to display the information.</p><h2>Hardware Components</h2><ul><li><p><strong>ESP8266 Module:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Selected for its compact size and Wi-Fi capabilities, serving as the central unit to fetch weather data.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>NeoPixel LED Strip:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Chosen for its individually addressable and vibrant RGB color capabilities.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h2>Data Retrieval and Integration</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Open Meteo API:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Integrated the Open Meteo API to retrieve weather forecast data for a specific location, providing access to precipitation probability information.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h2>Data Processing and Display</h2><ul><li><p><strong>JSON Parsing:</strong></p><ul><li><p>The program parses the JSON response from the API to extract hourly precipitation probability data for display on NeoPixel LEDs.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Looped Operation:</strong></p><ul><li><p>The program operates in a continuous loop, fetching and displaying updated weather information every hour.</p></li></ul></li></ul><hr><p></p>"}},"pageContext":{"id":"DatoCmsPage-M3_8ulpRSVmejKy0HNjlPg","slug":"brolli","__params":{"slug":"brolli"}}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{"footer":"footer","header":"header"}}